article.headline: Illinois State 65, Evansville 57
article.story: NORMAL, Ill. (AP) -- Nedu Onyeuku came off the bench to score 14 points and help lead Illinois State to a 65-57 victory over Evansville in Missouri Valley Conference action Monday night. Playing before more than 4,100 home fans at Redbird Arena, Illinois State (7-9, 2-6 Missouri Valley Conference) took a 33-20 advantage into halftime and held off the Aces after the break for the win. Shy Ely led Evansville (5-10, 1-6) with 14 points. Kyle Anslinger added 12 points, and Jason Holsinger had 10. In addition to Onyeuku, three other Redbirds scored in double digits. Khalif Ford had 11 points, while Greg Dilligard and Michael Vandello each had 10.
